Param/Value/lib_22142002_E4CD3FF3=This is how this command works: "-weapon (add/remove) <value of unit's name of which you wish to add the weapon from>". In the weapons list which may be added may be found: most unlockable units within the regular sc2 campaigns excluding the Nova campaign, and miscellaneous units such as the swarm host or the baneling ; and mercenaries. If a unit has 1 weapon it may be refered to by its name in lower case, such as "marine". If a unit has more weapons it may be refered to like this: "viking1" and "viking2". No units will not have their hidden weapons added, and if a unit has more variations under the same name - that have different weapons, they may be added via adding part of its subtitle prefix: "zealot", "aiurzealot". You may not add weapons to a unit that has 3 or more weapons. A unit can't have multiple of the same weapon. If a unit that isn't miscellaneous isn't added, then it would have been too problematic be added.
